Visit patek.com to view this four part series that explores the mechanics of the Sky Moon Tourbillon. In total, this extraordinary timepiece combines 12 fascinating complications, including a tourbillon and a minute repeater that strikes on cathedral gongs.

The reverse side of the case reveals the course of the moon, with sidereal time, sky chart, phases, and orbit of the moon.

#PatekTime

With its sporty casual and elegant look, the Aquanaut is a favorite amongst international travelers, constantly on-the-go.

The new Aquanaut Luce Travel Time presents itself as a true travel companion.

It features two hour hands – one pierced for home time, the other solid for local time.

When changing time zones, the hour hand for local time may be set forwards or backwards by increments of one hour using the crown.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce

node.text:
The new Ref. 5236 In-line Perpetual Calendar opens up a new chapter in the storied history of Patek Philippe calendar timepieces, with the addition of a totally new perpetual calendar wristwatch with an innovative patented one-line display that displays the day, the date, and the month on a single line. 

While seemingly simple, the in-line display presented a highly complex technical challenge and the development of a new movement (caliber 31-260 PS QL) for which three patent applications have been filed.  

#PatekPhilippe #PerpetualCalendar #PatekTime

The new Ref. 5236 In-line Perpetual Calendar houses the new self-winding movement caliber 31-260 PS QL. PS for ‘petite seconde’ [subsidiary seconds] and QL for ‘quantième perpétuel en ligne’ [in-line perpetual calendar]). The seemingly simple in-line display presented a highly complex technical challenge and development of three patented innovations.

The movement consists of 503 parts, 298 of which are dedicated to the perpetual calendar function. In the assembly process, a ‘test’ dial is used to ensure the optimal functionality of the in-line display.

node.text:
With the introduction of these new timepieces, Patek Philippe creates an eclectic bouquet of novelties - ranging from the much awaited, casual elegant Nautilus collection, new additions to the timelessly elegant Calatrava collection, a totally new Grand Complication and an addition to the ingenious patented Annual Calendar collection.
 
The introduction of these new references reflect the Manufacture’s extensive mastery of technical complexity, without sacrificing a perfect aesthetic.

“If you want to preserve your independence, you must have a fantastic product, and to have a fantastic product, you have to control the quality that goes inside. To do that, you have to do it yourself. We have been evolving in terms of quantity, in terms of complexity, and we needed more space, more tools, more people, more machines.

This is why we decided at one point, in 2013, to think about the future of Patek Philippe, by having a new building.”

Thierry Stern, President, Patek Philippe

node.text:
The Patek Philippe Diamond Ribbon Ref. 4968 created on the inspiration of a spiralling gymnast’s ribbon, requires unique techniques to produce the case design and meticulous diamond setting savoir-faire, perfectly balancing technical mechanical mastery and feminine allure.

Manually wound mechanical movement caliber 215 PS LU.

node.text:
Watchmaking Artistry.

Patek Philippe has always considered its watches to be works of art. The quest for excellence and harmony comes to the fore in understated, elegant, and timeless designs. It is further emphasized by quality in craftsmanship and the manually executed finissage. With the same passion, Patek Philippe cultivates all techniques used to decorate timepieces, assuring that these skills are handed down from one generation to the next.

This manifestation of ancestral artisanship is not reserved exclusively for one-of-a-kind pieces and limited editions that, year after year, constitute a new rare handcrafts collection. Patek Philippe also perpetuates these skills in creating its current collection timepieces.

In June 2021, Patek Philippe introduced six new current collection models; a stunning ladies Nautilus high jewellery timepiece, the iconic Golden Ellipse adorned with Grand Feu champlevé enamel dial and four new rare handcrafts Minute Repeaters, including an exceptional Sky Moon Tourbillon Ref. 6002.

#PatekTime

Turn on the sound and listen closely...What time is it?

Minute Repeaters are one of the most fascinating and complex complications to master. Did you know their role originated in the need to be able to tell the time, in the dark before electrical power was available? 

In 2021, Patek Philippe’s long-lasting passion for chiming watches and mastery of these extremely complex mechanisms is once again reaffirmed.

Introducing four new rare handcrafts Minute Repeaters adorned with ancestral artisanal skills. From the purest of sound to the finest decorations, these timepieces reflect the refined aesthetics of mechanical perfection.

#PatekTime

12 fascinating complications, 2 faces. Infinite passion.

Most coveted by collectors and connoisseurs, Ref.6002 Sky Moon Tourbillon is Patek Philippe’s second most complicated wristwatch. 

The Manufacture has endowed this emblematic model with a new face, combining the warm shimmer of rose gold with a brown Grand Feu champlevé and cloisonné enamel dial.

Dive into the exquisite dance of hand-engraved volutes and arabesques that decorate the Patek Philippe’s emblematic Sky Moon Tourbillon Ref. 6002. 

The double-faced case, crowns, slide piece, hour/minute hands and fold-over clasp are entirely hand-engraved. With considerable skill and patience, the Patek Philippe artisan invests more than 100 hours of work to create this artwork. 

#PatekTime

Visit patek.com to view this four part series that explores the mechanics of the Sky Moon Tourbillon. In total, this extraordinary timepiece combines 12 fascinating complications, including a tourbillon and a minute repeater that strikes on cathedral gongs.

The reverse side of the case reveals the course of the moon, with sidereal time, sky chart, phases, and orbit of the moon.

#PatekTime

Delicate motifs and sparkling beauty.

Minute Repeater Ref. 7040 in white gold presents a contemporary yet timeless look, a highly refined exterior, and the beautiful melody of classic gongs.

The gold dial plate is hand-guilloched with a swirling pattern, then coated with transparent blue enamel revealing the underlying decoration, a rare handcrafts technique known as flinqué enamel.

The bezel is remarkably radiant with 168 flawless Top Wesselton brilliant-cut diamonds set in two offset rows using the Flamme® technique. Move on to the following post to discover more about this unique skill.

Housing self-winding caliber R 27 PS, the timepiece stands out with its thin profile, svelte case silhouette and also harmonious sound of its two classic gongs.
The 36mm diameter case makes this refined timepiece housing the most complex Minute Repeater movement an ideal and elegant companion particularly adapted for a woman’s wrist.

#PatekTime

The Flamme® gemsetting technique. 

With this exclusive and patented setting method, the artisan uses a sharp burin to cut notches in the gold between the individual stones so that the light can ignite the fire of the diamonds from below as well, enhancing the airiness of the precious creation.

Gemfitting, slotting of the rose gold, doming, and polishing are skills leveraged by the artist who creates these small masterpieces of brilliance and finesse. 

They add a new dimension to Patek Philippe's mastery in the domain of rare handcrafts.

#PatekTime

Ref. 5374 Grand Complication with minute repeater and perpetual calendar combines technical excellence and elegance in a new white gold version with a Grand Feu blue enamel dial featuring a glossy finish. 

The case shape is distinguished by its subtle interplay of curves and its concave bezel.
 
The self-winding caliber R 27 Q features a minute repeater that strikes on two cathedral gongs; their extended length of nearly twice the circumference of the movement produces a full, reverberant sound.

node.text:
A miracle of transparency revealing mechanical beauty.

Patek Philippe reinterprets the rare and unique timepiece Ref. 5304 as a new Haute Joaillerie version in rose gold.

Allowing a complete immersion into the mechanical heart of the watch, it features an ingenious system for displaying the day, month, and leap year cycle with transparent sapphire-crystal disks in which the respective displays stand out in white against the black background of the small apertures beneath them. 

The pierced leaf-shaped hands in black-lacquered white gold also enhance the view of the movement and its steel parts with beveled and polished edges that stand out beautifully against the rose gilt plates decorated with perlage.
 
To further refine the appeal of this timepiece, the case flanks, the lugs and the repeater slide are decorated with delicate white-gold inlays featuring leaf motifs.

#PatekTime

node.text:
An icon dressed in diamonds.

Combining the iconic Nautilus design with the finesse of Haute Joaillerie, Ref. 7118/1450 in white gold sparkles with the fire of 2553 flawless Top Wesselton brilliant-cut diamonds (~12.69 ct). 

To further refine its aesthetic appeal, Patek Philippe chose the extremely elaborate technique of snow-setting, also referred to as random pavé setting. The gemsetter places diamonds of different sizes side by side in a liberal fashion, making sure that as little of the gold matrix is visible between the individual stones. 

This is why each watch with a snow-setting is unique.

#PatekTime

node.text:
Timeless design. 

Patek Philippe enriches its current collection by combining the iconic design of the Golden Ellipse timepiece with a black Grand Feu champlevé enamel dial.

Two of the most venerable working methods (hand engraving and enamel) are used to decorate this timepiece. The dial plate in 18K gold is hollowed out to create the recesses that are filled with Grand Feu black enamel, using the champlevé technique. The gold areas left in relief are then entirely hand-engraved. 

The polished white-gold case creates a stunning contrast with the depth of the black enameled dial. The decor, with its volutes and arabesques ideally complements the inimitable case shape of the Golden Ellipse and emphasizes the harmonious proportions of the case that are inspired by the golden section, also referred to as the “Divine Proportion”.

#PatekTime
